---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { FAMILY } from '~/lib/family'
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '~/lib/siteConfig'
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`about — ${SITE_CONFIG.name}`}
  description={`About ${SITE_CONFIG.name} — a privacy-first PWA journal in the oriz family.`}
>
  <section class="spine prose-page">
    <p class="eyebrow chrome"><a href="/">oriz-journal</a> / about</p>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p class="lede">
      A privacy-first PWA journal in the <a href={FAMILY.rootOrigin}>oriz family</a>.
      Closes the door at 11pm. Rereads March before decisions.
    </p>

    <h2>What this is</h2>
    <p>
      A place to capture today, revisit a year, and notice who you&rsquo;re becoming.
      Daily, gratitude, learning, reading, travel, work, fitness, dream, research,
      and reflection — ten kinds of entry, one editor. TipTap markdown, libsodium
      sealed bytes, autosave every 4.5 seconds.
    </p>

    <h2>The seal</h2>
    <p>
      A small mark sits in the corner of every page. Solid when the entry is
      encrypted to disk, hollow while you&rsquo;re typing, and pulses while
      libsodium seals the bytes. It is the only animated element in the app.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy by default</h2>
    <p>
      Entries live in Firestore under your own user ID. Firestore rules enforce
      it server-side. Account deletion removes every Firestore document owned
      by your <code>uid</code>. No tracking across sessions, no selling of data,
      no required signup. Plaintext never leaves the device when E2EE is on.
    </p>

    <h2>What is not here</h2>
    <p>
      No streak counters, no flame icons, no &ldquo;don&rsquo;t break the chain&rdquo;
      nags. No AI features in the writing surface — no summarize, no sentiment,
      no auto-tag. No padlock icon — the seal is the privacy signal.
    </p>

    <h2>One sign-in, every site</h2>
    <p>
      The same identity works across every <code>*.oriz.in</code> site. Anonymous
      trial mode lets you start without an email; link an account later from
      <a href="/account/">/account</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Open source</h2>
    <p>
      Source: <a href={`https://github.com/${FAMILY.operator.githubHandle}/oriz-journal`}>github.com/{FAMILY.operator.githubHandle}/oriz-journal</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-page {
    padding-block: 3rem 4rem;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--graphite);
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .eyebrow a { color: var(--graphite); text-decoration: none; }
  .eyebrow a:hover { color: var(--seal-red); }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .lede {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--graphite);
    max-width: 50ch;
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  p { margin: 0 0 1rem; max-width: 66ch; }
  a { color: inherit; text-decoration-color: var(--seal-red); }
  a:hover { color: var(--seal-red); }
  code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875em;
    color: var(--graphite);
  }
</style>
